<TITLE> Pope says to make first visit to Africa in March </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 VATICAN CITY, Sun Oct 26, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pope Benedict said on Sunday he would visit Cameroon and Angola in March when he makes his first trip to Africa since becoming head of the Roman Catholic Church in 2005. The Pope announced the trip during a sermon closing a synod of the world's Roman Catholic bishops. He said he would travel to Cameroon to deliver the working document of a future synod whose theme will be Africa, and to Angola to celebrate 500 years of evangelisation there. Benedict's predecessor, John Paul II, travelled widely throughout Africa during his more than 26-year pontificate
